main event: On July 9, 1950, multiple unidentified objects with three lights were observed in Ocho Rios, Jamaica.
interesting points: The first object was described as a heavy trail oblong form heading at 120 degrees., A second, erratic object was also observed with three lights., The third object continued to be visible for around three minutes., These sightings occurred in an area known for considerable UFO activity., The conclusion speculated that the objects might be astronomical in nature.
sighted object: three unidentified flying objects with three lights each
witness description: A person reported observing the objects and indicated that no sound was made during the sighting.
